# Active Platform Scope

- Treat `iOS`, `Android`, and `Web` as the active in-scope product platforms for current implementation, QA, release, and debugging work.
- Do not proactively spend time on `macOS`, `Windows`, `Linux`, or desktop-specific behavior unless the user explicitly asks for it.
- When platform trade-offs come up, optimize first for mobile and web behavior, tooling, and UX.
- If a bug appears only on an out-of-scope desktop platform, note it briefly and move on unless the user wants it investigated.
- This scope is temporary and may change later, so keep decisions and docs easy to update.
